3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper derives asymptotics on the function that counts the number of weights in a cyclic code, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Cyclic codes are used in cryptography and error correction, which makes this paper relevant to the cryptography and security sub-category. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses the computation of the largest number of weights a cyclic code can have, which involves numerical analysis techniques.
